This paper deals with the restricted isometry property (RIP) in the context of Orthogonal Matching Pursuit (OMP), which is a popular algorithm in signal processing and compressive sensing. The paper provides a positive result on the conjecture given by Dai and Milenkovic in 2009, which is related to the RIP of the measurement matrix. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing. The paper also involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), respectively. Additionally, the paper deals with signal processing and compressive sensing, which are covered in cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing), respectively.
